Habitat. Mixed woodland and chaparral. Taken from twigs in tangles, poison oak, and California sage (
Artemisia californica Less.
). Males call approximately 1 m above ground level in thick tangles. At dusk two males and one female emerged for nocturnal activity from a pack rat nest, suggesting that this structure served as a daytime shelter for an aggregation of individuals. These individuals retreated into the nest when disturbed.
